iLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TaGFyay1SMTAwMUFFLVNlbGYtRW1wdHktQ29ubmVjdGVkLUNhcGFjaXR5L2RwL0IwN1M4NjRHUFc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMTRhLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3OTE3YzIyYS03ODg5LTRjMzItYTJkOS05NWFhY2RhMWQyMTEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVVsJHbpkTEqOcIriS8Bq-Iez1SUFllHcK1Mmk8OKNze&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FShark-R1001AE-Self-Empty-Connected-Capacity%2Fdp%2FB07S864GPW" class="rapid-with-clickid">Shark RV1001AE</a> is half price, making it $300 instead of its $600 street price. This model has a bagless, self-emptying base, that you won&#39;t have to empty for quite some time as it has a claimed capacity of up to 45 days. While we didn&#39;t try this exact model, we&#39;ve found vacs from Shark to be easy to set up and appreciate Shark&#39;s easy-to-use companion app. Shark&#39;s mapping function is also accurate and the bagless base will save you money in the long run as buying device-specific bags can get pricey.</p><h2> Samsung QN90B 55-inch 4K TV </h2><p><core-commerce id="11dc40472642454e83ce57a9ed3659e4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The 55-inch version of <a data-i13n="cpos:53;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbXAuJcKxA38d3gmb9vcnd20Jh52enmpmg2Zgmzz5XcT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09SBHSNNZ%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1%3Fsmid%3DATVPDKIKX0DER%26psc%3D1">Samsung&#39;s QN90B</a> , a recommendation from our <a data-i13n="cpos:54;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-tvs-for-gaming-180033983.html">gaming TV buying guide</a> , has dropped to $998. That&#39;s a new all-time low. Most reviews say this TV delivers enough brightness for well-lit rooms, with smooth motion performance and richer contrast than most non-OLED TVs thanks to its Mini LED backlighting. It also has four full HDMI 2.1 ports and can play up to 120 Hz in 4K. It still can&#39;t match the contrast, response time or viewing angles of a good OLED TV, but it should be better equipped for rooms plagued by glare. Like most Samsung TVs, however, it doesn&#39;t support Dolby Vision HDR. Samsung has replaced this 2022 model with the <a data-i13n="cpos:55;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwQlRUVkw0MTk_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMTRhLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3OTE3YzIyYS03ODg5LTRjMzItYTJkOS05NWFhY2RhMWQyMTEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAYY0-v-7BpJ80AHDhOfZpIYC2NtEvwBGcRoIPAOpR_as&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0BTTVL419">new QN90C</a> , but the 55-inch version of that set currently costs $600 more, so the QN90B remains the better value for the time being.</p><h2> Samsung Galaxy Watch 5 </h2><p><core-commerce id="82b39bb57d2e41dab1c787229046a5f2" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:56;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEIySjVUQjNRP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLTE0YS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNzkxN2MyMmEtNzg4OS00YzMyLWEyZDktOTVhYWNkYTFkMjExIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAWiQntQfuL-DpTNEDx9m5QPh_cN-L6WPbhTNq0SxIGRo&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B2J5TB3Q">Samsung Galaxy Watch 5</a> is down to $229 for a 40mm model and $259 for a <a data-i13n="cpos:57;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEIySjRXNVRUP3RoPTEmdGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMTRhLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3OTE3YzIyYS03ODg5LTRjMzItYTJkOS05NWFhY2RhMWQyMTEifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAU1TmQmGcWLZhjXtQLGpqR2ggaG5X4r_eZuqNKt3fF-7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B2J4W5TT%3Fth%3D1">44mm model</a> . Neither deal represents an all-time low, but both are within $10 of their best prices to date. We gave the Galaxy Watch 5 a <a data-i13n="cpos:58;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-5-pro-review-battery-life-specs-durability-180052187.html">score of 85</a> last year, and it&#39;s currently the &quot;best for Android users&quot; pick in our <a data-i13n="cpos:59;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smartwatches-153013118.html">smartwatch buying guide</a> . While its battery life could be better, its design is durable and attractive, its OS is easy to navigate and its health tracking is relatively comprehensive. Samsung is expected to announce a <a data-i13n="cpos:60;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-watch-6-leak-suggests-the-rotating-bezel-will-return-124637657.html">Galaxy Watch 6</a> in the coming weeks, however, so it may be worth waiting to see how that model stacks up if you don&#39;t need a new smartwatch right this instant.</p><h2> Google Pixel 7a + Pixel Buds A-Series </h2><p><core-commerce id="bc03f3966efb4f8381f72684ce1d5060" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Amazon knocked $100 off a bundle that includes the <a data-i13n="cpos:61;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUEmoHTd7IM41V8YPjc4ugbl9KKmEQ5JFRVAtyp_zVOe&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-7a-128GB-Charcoal-Pixel%2Fdp%2FB0C7WB7FGS">Google Pixel 7a smartphone and the Pixel Buds A-Series</a> , bringing it down to $499. This is a great bundle if you&#39;ve needed a phone upgrade but didn&#39;t want to spend a ton of money. The Pixel 7a is the <a data-i13n="cpos:62;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-engadget-guide-to-the-best-midrange-smartphones-120050366.html">best midrange phone</a> you can get right now, thanks to its fast Tensor G2 chipset, smooth 90Hz display, IP67 water resistance, fantastic cameras and support for wireless charging. The <a data-i13n="cpos:63;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-buds-a-series-review-160054961.html">Pixel Buds A-Series</a> are almost the earbud-complement to the Pixel 7a — they&#39;re not as feature-rich as the Pixel Buds Pro, but they have deep Google Assistant integration, solid sound quality and a comfy fit.</p><p> <strong><em>Your Prime Day Shopping Guide:</em></strong> <em>See all of our</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:64;pos:1" href="https://www.yahoo.com/topics/prime-day/"><em>Prime Day</em></a> <em>coverage. Shop the</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:65;pos:1" href="https://www.yahoo.com/lifestyle/prime-day-2023-191047652.html"><em>best Prime Day deals</em></a> <em>on Yahoo Life. Follow Engadget for the</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:66;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-prime-day-2023-124519231.html"><em>best Amazon Prime Day tech deals</em></a> <em>. Learn about</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:67;pos:1" href="https://www.intheknow.com/tag/prime-day/"><em>Prime Day trends</em></a> <em>on In th